  "text": "The following ASL parameters were used for quantitative cerebellum perfusion studies: FOV = 180 × 180 mm 2 , matrix size = 72 × 72, slice thickness/gap = 3.5/0.7 mm, slice number = 16, in-plane resolution = 2.5 × 2.5 mm 2 , slice thickness/gap = 3.5/0.7 mm, TR/TE = 2500/12 ms, pairs of label and control measurements = 90, iPAT GRAPPA factor = 2 with 24 reference lines, partial Fourier (PF) = 7/8, acquisition order = ascending (foot to head), 1 / 2 = 800 ms/1800 ms, inferior saturation interval/thickness/number = 25 ms/20 mm/20, superior saturation slab thickness = 100 mm, selective inversion slab = 86.5 mm, and spatially confined inversion slab = 266.5 mm. For PICORE, a 100 mm slab, approximately the same as the effective inferior labeling slab size applied in FAIR ASST experiments, was used for proximal inversion, with a 10 mm gap between the imaging slab and the inversion slab. For each ASL scan, two proton density ( 0 ) images were acquired, one before and one after each ASL series, by using the same sequence with TR = 8 s, and the average 0 image was used in subsequent model fits [CITATION_1] . The total ASL imaging scan time was about 16 minutes with about 8 minutes for each method.",
